            <h3>Victorias City’s Must Do List</h3>
            <ol><li>1. Stay in Gawahon Eco-Park and experience what Victorias City’s nature has to offer. It has seven pristine waterfalls, a magnificent upland view of the City and a fresh cool breeze from the mountain top.
                </li><li>2. See the “Angry Christ” mural, a world-famed liturgical art masterpiece done by Alfonso Ossorio, artist-son of VMC founder Don Miguel Ossorio. It is located inside the church of St. Joseph the Worker. The “Angry Christ” shows craggy- faced Christ in bold primary colors.
                </li><li>3. Tour Victorias Milling Company’s huge agro-industrial complex which was established in 1919. It was the first sugar mill in the Philippines to earn ISO 9002 certification.
                </li><li>4. Play at the VMC Golf and Country Club, an 18-hole golf course, which is a challenging place for golf aficionados. 5. Enjoy the City’s Malihaw Festival in April and Kadalag-an festivals in March.
